GASIFICATION_SECTION
1    ! Units for E only for gasification:   1 = kJ/kmol;  2 = kJ/mol;   3 = kcal/mol  4 = cal/mol

! Particle component X gasification rates    Xsolid (Xs) -> Xgas (Xg)
! Rate (kg/s) =   k * Xs^x * Y^y * Sp^s * (Mp/Mpo)^m
! Xs = mass fraction of particle component X in solid particle
! Y  = mass fraction of any relevant gas phase species eg O2 
! Sp = particle surface area (m)
! Mp/Mpo = particle mass/initial particle mass 

!  rateconst k  = A * Tp^t  * EXP[-E /(Rgas*Tp)]  
! Tp  = particle T

 
! Species X   species Y           A      t     E           x      y       s       m    
